      About this item

      • SMART MOTION DETECTION AND AI RECOGNITION: The rechargeable wireless outdoor security camera utilizes AI smart sensors, which can recognize people, pets, vehicles and package drop-offs. The security cameras wireless outdoor use an infrared sensor, it will detect motion and send notifications to your mobile phone in real-time.
      • 100% WIRELESS AND LONG LIFE BATTERY: The cameras for home security with a built-in rechargeable battery, it can provide 1 to 6 months of worry free use before a recharge is required. The outdoor camera wireless needn't any wires, the installation is very simple and it's waterproof, which can be installed in anywhere.
      • 1080P HD LIVE VIDEO AND COLOR NIGHT VISION: This security camera provides 1080P quality video and image. It will automatically adjust to the ambient light level and when necessary. At night, it will auto-switch to color night vision effected of up to 33ft visible range, provides a wide clear vision.
      • TWO-WAY AUDIO, INSTANT SIRE, SPOTLIGHT: This wireless security camera outdoor has a built-in microphone and speaker, you can make 2-way audio calls in real-time. The instant siren, flashing white light and 2-way talk can drive away thieves and unwanted visitors.
      • SUPPORT SD CARD AND FREE 3-DAY CYCLE CLOUD STORAGE: The home security camera supports SD card and cloud storage. It provides free rolling 3-day cycled cloud storage that you can enjoy storage service without any subscription. It provides a 30-day free trial of advanced features that include AI recognition, upgraded cloud memory, custom alert areas, etc, the advanced features start at $2.99 per month after a 30-days free trial.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Better than my Vivint Cameras
      I just got my third camera and so I decided to make a review because these guys are great. In fact check the photo out in my review I just snapped that with the app and that's how crystal clear my front yard looks at night. I have several cameras around the house that all have a similar HD crisp clear quality. I have less issues and less lag time and buffering with these cameras than my expensive Vivint cameras. These are also easy to install. First out of the box don't do anything but charge it up for about 3 or 4 hours. Then have the app all set up open up the app and get to the section where you want to add a device. Hold the power on the camera down for a long press and you'll hear a beep and some other things while the camera connects up to the app. Do all that on your couch or while you're laying in your bed so you don't have to be stressed out outside trying to put the camera up while you're turning it on. The screws are sharp enough if you have a little bit of muscle you can take a Phillips and the screw and just muscle it into the wood of course I'm talking about the camera attachment receptacle not the camera itself. If you have to put the camera upside down no problem because on the app you have a thing that you can do to rotate it I believe it's a button that you just click and I will rotate the camera in the right direction for you. For the small amount of money these are it's amazing how long the battery lasts. My first camera battery seems to be better than the second one I charged it up last October and it still has 30% left battery. I don't know how I can last from October until February and still have 30% remaining but it does. I guess I got lucky. My second camera I put up at the beginning of January and it's already at 50% after 1 month so although that's still very good it's not as good as my original first camera.

      • ckmoore
        4.0 out of 5 stars So far, so good (2 camera set).
        Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2024
        Color: 2-PackVerified Purchase
        I was looking for an inexpensive camera system to monitor my driveway and front porch and these seemed to fit the bill. Overall, I am very pleased with my choice. I have had them for roughly 2 weeks and want to offer my initial impressions.

        Pros: Price / value, image quality, low light capability, wide angle field of view, SD card and cloud storage options, can be mounted in upright or hanging positions. Easy enough to set up. Settings are highly customizable.

        Cons: ( Lengthy explanation, but hopefully helpful. ) I have one camera pointed down on my front porch and the second on my driveway. I noticed right away that I was getting constant alerts and recordings from my driveway camera, sometimes a few minutes apart. The battery on that camera was draining quickly, needing to be charged twice in over 2 weeks. In comparison, the porch camera is still reading 89% 2 weeks later after the initial charge. I believe I discovered the problem. Because these are wide angle cameras and motion activated, it was picking up every car, pedestrian, and squirrel that entered its field of view. It also recorded my flag moving, also in view. I moved my flag, and trained the camera down on the driveway as much as possible restricting as much of the street and sidewalk as I could. Those changes drastically reduced the number of recordings and should give me similar battery performance to the other camera. Time will tell. I have yet to see how long a battery charge lasts, but 2 to 3 months seems possible. Solar panel chargers didn't work for me since I have a northern exposure, but would be a worthwhile choice if you get sunlight where the cameras are placed. Cloud storage plans are based on the number of cameras used. You get one month free trial and then an annual subscription if you decide to go that route.

        I think these should meet my needs just fine, but if I had them in high-traffic areas I would probably opt for a different set up. I hope this helps.
